							<div class="span6">
								<img id="ayden" class="right" src="images/Ayden.png" alt="Ayden" />
								<p>On <span class="red">XX</span> March 2013, 14 year old Ayden Olson took his own life. He&#39;d been bullied to death. 
								Tragically, Ayden&#39;s name is only the latest to be added to a growing list. 
								But while the victims themselves may have found peace, their families are left behind, 
								scarred forever by the agony of losing a child.
								</p>
								<p>Ayden&#39;s Law is a campaign on behalf of all those young people, their families – 
								and any child or young person being bullied today.
								</p>
								<p>BeatBullying, The Sun, and families of children like Ayden are calling on David Cameron to take action. 
								We want the Prime Minister to call a summit to discuss how we can prevent any more tragedies – 
								and the creation of Ayden&#39;s Law, a new children&#39;s anti-bullying bill 
								designed to stop bullying in our society once and for all.
								</p>
								<p class="gap_below">Read <a href="letter_to_pm.html" target="_blank">our letter to David Cameron</a>.</p>
							</div>
